Subject: Re: [T2] 1973 vw automatic bus.. how to mount engine?

> I notice I can push down (toward ground) on rear (pulley) end of
> engine, and the engine/tranny will rock (pivoting on transmission
> rear mount, which is to frame)..


All bays require a crosmember at the engine. The trans mounts aren't
enough to hold it all together like a bug.

Get a 72 or later engine mount bar and start cutting and welding to
get it to mount to your Subie. Or fab something from scratch.

And somewhere in between is what you want.

